According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Airline Catering Market was valued at USD 5.0 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 5.35 billion in 2025 to USD 7.91 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth due to the strong recovery in European air passenger traffic, increasing demand for premium onboard dining experiences, and the growing adoption of sustainable catering solutions. Airlines are also investing in personalized meal services, healthier menu options, and eco-friendly packaging to enhance passenger satisfaction while meeting stringent European environmental regulations.
